
[1]death-bed

   DEATH-BED, n. deth'-bed. The bed on which a person dies or is confined
   in his last sickness.

   DEATH'-BODING, a. Portending death.

   DEATH-DARTING, a. Darting or inflicting death.

   DEATH'S-DOOR, n. A near approach to death; the gates of death.

   DEATH'FUL, a. Full of slaughter; murderous; destructive.
